                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-392-defend2035 t18260914-392-deflabel2199"></join>. On the 12th of August, about a quarter-past eleven o'clock, I sent him to the Excise-office to pay some duty, with ten sovereigns, four shillings, and two penny-pieces; he had the charge-paper with him; he never returned; I found him on board a ship in the river, and had him secured; I could not get a word out of him; the Captain said, in his presence, he had paid his passage with one sovereign and a shilling, for Yorkshire; he had eight sovereigns and 17s. 6d. in his pocket, which he gave up.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-392-person2037">
